  "text": "The present study has limitations. First, ischemia of the subcortical white matter could not be demonstrated on the ASL imaging, since quantitative measurements of CBF could not be achieved by the single PLD methods [CITATION_1] . Furthermore, the arterial transit artifacts [CITATION_2] of the cortical hyperperfusion were strong enough to extend to the level of the subcortex. Second, our experience is limited to a single AED case with a monophasic clinical course. Further studies with serial ASL examinations are required. Our findings suggest that the finding of prolonged ASL hyperperfusion around day 4 after SE may be important for the detection of AED or AESD development.",
